Name: SOLDERING
Description: Lead-Tin alloy melts to join wires permanently | Wetting/Conductivity

Name: THERMAL_CRACKING
Description: Heat and pressure break heavy oil molecules into gasoline | Molecular Cracking

Name: ALUMINUM_SMELTING
Description: Electricity separates metal from ore (Hall-Heroult) | Electrolysis

Name: ARC_WELDING
Description: Electric arc melts metal edges to fuse them into one piece | Fusion Joining

Name: TITANIUM_REFINING
Description: Extracting light/strong metal from ore using magnesium/chlorine | Kroll Process

Name: HABER_BOSCH
Description: Nitrogen from air -> Ammonia (Fertilizer/Explosives) | High Pressure Catalysis

Name: LEATHER_TANNING
Description: Tannins soften skin and stop rot | Preservation

Name: STEEL_BESSEMER
Description: Air blown through iron burns off carbon | Oxidation

Name: GALVANIZATION
Description: Zinc coating protects steel | Electrochemical Protection

Name: OIL_REFINING
Description: Crude oil separated by boiling points | Fractional Distillation
